gm-method (implicivity audit paradigm, 2026-06): maximizing prose implicivity = convert passages that DESCRIBE a procedure (numbered recipes, do-X-then-Y, trigger-instance lists, over-explained rationale, restated code-mechanism) into a CONSTRUCTED PREDICAMENT that elicits the disposition (a framing where the wrong move is structurally incoherent / self-evidently loses), so the agent re-derives the action under any edge case instead of imitating a script that breaks. HARD GUARD: never reduce functionality -- the boot-edge ABI (exact spool paths, JSON field names, verb names, file globs, deviation identifiers, gate names) is non-derivable mechanism a wrong guess breaks and MUST stay explicit; only DERIVABLE procedure converts. The audit method that worked: one subagent per prose surface returns structured findings {passage, classification(describes-procedure|over-explains|restates-code-mechanism|enumerates-instances|already-implicit-leave), why, predicament-rewrite, lever-preservation-argument}; an ADVERSARIAL verify agent per finding (default-skeptic, accept|accept-with-edit|reject) catches over-implicitization (a rewrite so terse it drops a lever or no longer drives the action). For accept-with-edit, apply the verifier's tightened intent (restore the flagged lever), not the raw rewrite. Witnessed: 10 gm prose surfaces audited, prose already strongly implicit overall, 24 surgical rewrites landed, test.js PASS, AGENTS.md byte-count dropped.